{"parentUuid":"6c33a592-4ceb-4f2e-884b-8b3bd47e79b6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019mfZNbFprghAb4dSSxUEXA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Mutex** — mutual exclusion lock. Binary (locked/unlocked). Only the thread that acquired it can release it. Enforces ownership.\n\n**Semaphore** — a counter. Initialized to N, any thread can signal (increment) or wait (decrement). No ownership concept.\n\nKey differences:\n\n| | Mutex | Semaphore |\n|---|---|---|\n| Values | 0 or 1 | 0 to N |\n| Ownership | Yes — only owner unlocks | No — any thread can signal |\n| Use case | Protect a single shared resource | Limit concurrent access to N resources |\n| Example | One thread writing to a file | Connection pool of 10 DB connections |\n\nA mutex is like a bathroom key — one person takes it, only they return it. A semaphore is like a parking lot with N spots — anyone can enter if spots remain, anyone leaving frees a spot."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30293,"cache_read_input_tokens":15866,"output_tokens":236,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30293,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZPUTD4YKRjuPLroFcAzS","type":"assistant","uuid":"f82eefd5-282e-42cc-8f25-0c591b25477f","timestamp":"2026-03-25T08:21:51.204Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain-v1/el-paso-v1","sessionId":"b34557da-b22e-4be7-ab73-9d474e911b5f","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"marcus-sa/sandbox-agent-eval"}
